### [](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_version_information){.anchor}[1.1. Updates & Announcements](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_version_information){.link} {#_version_information}

::: paragraph
USA: Requirements for shipments

::: content
For shipments to the USA, the following requirements apply:

-   **Additional contract agreement.**
-   **User consent** to pay customs duty and administration fees.
-   In Self-Service, API v2 users must edit their profile and check "I
    agree to pay customs duty and commission fee" (one-time action).
-   If consent is given → users can create shipments to the USA via API
    v2 and Self-Service.
-   If not → shipments to the USA are blocked, except for "documents
    only," which can be created without customs declaration.
-   Users can check duty fee amounts using the new `duty/estimate/price`
    and existing `shipping/estimate/price` endpoints.

[See request
examples](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_dutyestimateprice){.btn}
:::

USA: Duty Fee & Full Shipping Cost Endpoints (incl. Customs &
Administration Fees)

::: content
New ways to calculate costs are now available:

-   Retrieve only customs duty and administration fees via
    duty/estimate/price.
-   Retrieve full shipping cost including customs duty and
    administration fees via shipping/estimate/price

[See request
examples](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_dutyestimateprice){.btn}
:::

Mandatory HS Code & Country of Origin in documents.cn.parts

::: content
In the [Create
Parcel](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_parcelrequests)
request, fields in documents.cn.parts become required:

-   hsCode --- 6, 8, or 10 digits
-   countryCode --- country of origin
:::

::: content
Effective dates\

-   USA shipments: required now
-   All other non-EU destinations: required from 2025-12-15

[See request
examples](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_parcelrequests){.btn}
:::

International S/M parcels: use \"Tracked\" --- from 2025-12-15
\"Signed\" only for documents.

::: content
Starting 15 December 2025, the **Registered Correspondence
(\"Signed\")** service (S and M sizes) will remain available **only for
sending documents**.

This restriction applies to all international destinations.

**Within Lithuania**, the service will continue to be available without
changes.

[See request
examples](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_parcelrequests){.btn}
:::

New Service: Insurance for \"Tracked\" Plan

::: content
Starting **2025-12-15**, the **\"Tracked\"** shipping plan will include
an option to add **Insurance** for your parcels.

[See request
examples](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#BasicServiceCodes){.btn}
:::

Mandatory Description for EU Shipments

::: content
When sending parcels to EU countries, it is now required to provide a
detailed description of the parcel contents.

+-----------------+-----------------------------------+-----------------+
| Origin          | Destination                       | Description     |
|                 |                                   | Required        |
+=================+===================================+=================+
| LT              | LT                                | ❌ No           |
+-----------------+-----------------------------------+-----------------+
| LT              | Other EU countries                | ✅ Yes          |
+-----------------+-----------------------------------+-----------------+
| LV              | LV                                | ❌ No           |
+-----------------+-----------------------------------+-----------------+
| LV              | Other EU countries                | ✅ Yes          |
+-----------------+-----------------------------------+-----------------+
| EE              | EE                                | ❌ No           |
+-----------------+-----------------------------------+-----------------+
| EE              | Other EU countries                | ✅ Yes          |
+-----------------+-----------------------------------+-----------------+

The shipment description must be provided in the
parcel.content.items\[\].summary field.

[See request
examples](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_parcelrequests){.btn}
:::

Order a return service (generates an additional label for sending the
parcel back)

::: content
When adding the PRODUCT_RETURN service in the [services
object](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#BasicServiceCodes)
during [parcel
creation](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_create), an
additional return label will be generated. This return label will be
provided together with the original parcel label.

You can create return labels by submitting one or multiple original
shipment barcodes. A return barcode is generated for each.

Availability:\
Applicable for shipping plans H2H, T2H, T2T, H2T, H2P\
Valid only for shipments between the Baltic countries (LT, LV, EE)

To enable return label generation for your shipments, please contact
your sales manager.

[See request
examples](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#BasicServiceCodes){.btn}
:::
:::
:::

::: sect2
### [](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_getting_started){.anchor}[1.2. Getting started!](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_getting_started){.link} {#_getting_started}

::: paragraph
This documentation provides all the basic information you need to start
using the UNISEND (LP EXPRESS) API. It covers not only how to find
streets, building, localities, addresses and buildings in Lithuania but
as well how to create a shipping item, how to manage all the process of
sending it from start to the end by calling the courier and creating
required documents for the shipment.
:::

::: paragraph
We offer a TEST environment of UNISEND (LP EXPRESS) which mimics the
PRODUCTION environment, so developers who integrate the public UNISEND
(LP EXPRESS) API to their application can experiment and test the
product without any consequences.
:::

::: {.note .ulist}
-   [https://api-manosiuntostst.post.lt](https://api-manosiuntostst.post.lt/){.bare}
    (test environment)

-   [https://api-manosiuntos.post.lt](https://api-manosiuntos.post.lt/){.bare}
    (production environment)
:::

::: paragraph
**Note**: At this step you already have to have authentication to the
TEST environment. We will provide you with the authentication to the
PRODUCTION environment when you will be done with the integration in the
TEST environment and all your needs have been reached ensuring that
everything is working as it should.
:::

::: paragraph
All the communication with the API must be authenticated. Only
authenticated request will be authorized. See **Authorization** page for
detailed information about used security.
:::

::: paragraph
One of the most important function of this API is to let the user
create, manage and send an item by creating it, adding required
documents, calling the courier and tracking it. The processes of doing
so are visualized bellow. As well find all the needed API methods and
data structures for creating a request for the API.
:::

::: {.imageblock .text-center}
::: content
:::
:::

::: paragraph
**Note**: As well we are giving you a [base requests
collection](https://www.post.lt/sites/default/files/APIV2/API%20v2%20Guidelines.postman_collection.json.zip)
for POSTMAN, which will help you with trying out the test environment of
the API. All the needed actions to do are:
:::

::: {.olist .arabic}
1.  Use(POST): Authorization(Without client secret) script. In the
    **params** tab add your credentials.

2.  You will get a response which will contain access token. Add it to
    your collection, select: View more actions → Edit
    →Authorization→Token
:::

::: paragraph
**Note**: another alternative to test API is a
[Swagger](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/%3Chostname%3E/api/v2/swagger-ui/index.html?urls.primaryName=LPExpress%20public%20API){target="_blank"}
running on our side.
:::

### [](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_authorization){.anchor}[1.3. Authorization](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_authorization){.link} {#_authorization}

::: {.olist .arabic}
1.  Authorization

    ::: paragraph
    Authorization of the users of the application programming interface
    uses the OAuth2 login standard. More information at
    [https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6749](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6749){.bare}
    :::

    ::: imageblock
    ::: content
    ![wdpMYg30+b1sgAAAABJRU5ErkJggg==](data:image/png;base64,)
    :::
    :::

2.  Getting started to use API\
    Contact before <api-manosiuntos@post.lt> authorizing to API, we need
    to make configuration on our side.

    ::: {.olist .loweralpha}
    a.  Getting access/refresh token

        ::: imageblock
        ::: content
        ![hxgAAAAASUVORK5CYII=](data:image/png;base64,)
        :::
        :::

    b.  Sample request to get access token:

        ::: paragraph
        **Tip**: Pass `API_CLIENT` scope to test API access.
        :::

        ::: listingblock
        ::: content
        ``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
        curl --location --request POST 'https://<hostname>/oauth/token?grant_type=password&username=<username>&password=<password>&scope=read%2Bwrite%2BAPI_CLIENT'
        ```
        :::
        :::

        ::: paragraph
        Sample response:
        :::

        ::: listingblock
        ::: content
        ``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
                                                                {
                                                                "access_token": "XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX",
                                                                "refresh_token": "YYYY-YYYY-YYYY-YYYY-YYYY",
                                                                "scope": "read write",
                                                                "token_type": "Bearer",
                                                                "expires_in": 2591999
                                                                }
                                                            
        ```
        :::
        :::

    c.  Sample request to get refresh token:

        ::: listingblock
        ::: content
        ``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
        curl --location --request POST 'https://<hostname>/oauth/token?grant_type=refresh_token&refresh_token=YYYY-YYYY-YYYY-YYYY-YYYY'
        ```
        :::
        :::

        ::: paragraph
        Sample response:
        :::

        ::: listingblock
        ::: content
        ``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
                                                                {
                                                                "access_token": "XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX",
                                                                "refresh_token": "YYYY-YYYY-YYYY-YYYY-YYYY",
                                                                "scope": "read write",
                                                                "token_type": "Bearer",
                                                                "expires_in": 2591999
                                                                }
                                                            
        ```
        :::
        :::

        ::: paragraph
        When you receive the access token, it have included a refresh
        token as well as an expiration time. The "expires_in" value is
        the number of seconds that the access token will be valid.
        Access tokens can expire for many reasons, such as the user
        revoking an app, or if the authorization server expires all
        tokens when a user changes their password.
        :::

        ::: paragraph
        If you make an API request and the token has expired already,
        you'll get back a response indicating 401 error.
        :::

        ::: paragraph
        You can check for this specific error message, and then refresh
        the token and try the request again. When your application
        recognizes this specific error, it can then make a request to
        the token endpoint using the refresh token it previously
        received, and will get back a new access token it can use to
        retry the original request.
        :::

        ::: paragraph
        The "expires_in" property refers to the access token, not the
        refresh token. The expiration time of the refresh token is
        intentionally never communicated to the client. This is because
        the client has no actionable steps it can take even if it were
        able to know when the refresh token would expire. There are also
        many reasons refresh tokens may expire prior to any expected
        lifetime of them as well.
        :::

    d.  **Important**: after 5 times invalid authentifications account
        will be blocked for 15 minutes.
    :::
:::
:::

Shipping item creation and management process](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_shipping_item_creation_and_management_process){.link} {#_shipping_item_creation_and_management_process}

::: paragraph
General overview of API shipping workflow
:::

::: imageblock
::: content
![L0U8o+8vU8VVQfrALAQjYTQDBbXf9iN4uAj9S4da2K2SihQAEPBCQC10EtwdQLIFAUgkguJNaefIuBoH6yun3i+EYnxCAQKAEpIO+UR2BddIDjR7jEIBA4AT+P+iMTh+eA+x3AAAAAElFTkSuQmCC](data:image/png;base64,)

::: sect2
### [](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_shipping_item_creation_full_example){.anchor}[2.1. Step-by-Step example.](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_shipping_item_creation_full_example){.link} {#_shipping_item_creation_full_example}

#### 0. Estimate parcel data

::: paragraph
Consider that we need to send a package **to the recipient\'s address**
within Lithuania by dispatching the package **from parcel locker**.

Based on the table in the [2.2. Plan
codes](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_plan_codes) section,
we find that the T2H plan type and the HANDS plan code match the
shipping method we require (from the parcel locker to the recipient\'s
address).
:::

You can find more details about plans, shipping rates, available
services, and other information using the EstimateShippingOperations
methods:

::: listingblock
::: content
``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
curl --location --request GET '/api/v2/shipping/estimate/plan?receiverCountryCode=LT&senderCountryCode=LT'
```
:::
:::

#### 1. Parcel creation step

::: listingblock
::: content
``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
curl --location --request POST '/api/v2/parcel'
```
:::
:::

[Request Body ]{.clickonme}

::: content
::: listingblock
::: content
``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
                            
                                {
                                    "plan": {
                                      "code": "HANDS"
                                    },
                                    "parcel": {
                                      "type":"T2H",
                                      "size":"S"
                                    },
                                    "receiver": {
                                      "name": "test name",
                                      "companyName": "test lastName",
                                      "address": {
                                          "countryCode": "LT",
                                          "locality":"Vilnius",
                                          "postalCode": "08247",
                                          "street": "Juozo Balčikonio g.",
                                          "building": "3"
                                      },
                                      "contacts":{
                                          "phone":"+37000000000",
                                          "email": "test@test.lt"
                                      }
                                    }
                                  }
                            
                        
```
:::
:::
:::

[Request Body by idRef\* ]{.clickonme}

::: content
::: listingblock
::: content
``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
                            
                                {   
                                    "idRef": "YOUR_ORORDER_ID_123",
                                    "plan": {
                                      "code": "HANDS"
                                    },
                                    "parcel": {
                                      "type":"T2H",
                                      "size":"S"
                                    },
                                    "receiver": {
                                      "name": "test name",
                                      "companyName": "test lastName",
                                      "address": {
                                          "countryCode": "LT",
                                          "locality":"Vilnius",
                                          "postalCode": "08247",
                                          "street": "Juozo Balčikonio g.",
                                          "building": "3"
                                      },
                                      "contacts":{
                                          "phone":"+37000000000",
                                          "email": "test@test.lt"
                                      }
                                    }
                                  }
                            
                        
```
:::
:::
:::

::: paragraph
\* The \"idRef\" parameter acts as a unique identifier for parcels in
the system, allowing for simplified management by referencing a
user-specified value instead of system-generated parcelId.
:::

[Response Body ]{.clickonme}

::: content
::: listingblock
::: content
``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
                            
                                {
                                    "parcelId": 3499918,
                                    "warnings": []
                                }
                            
                        
```
:::
:::
:::

#### 2. Parcel update step

::: paragraph
If corrections need to be made, such as correcting the address, plan,
size, weight, services and etc., you can update the parcel by simply
resending the request with the new information, specifying the parcelId
obtained in the response from the previous step.
:::

::: listingblock
::: content
``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
curl --location --request PUT '/api/v2/parcel/{parcelId}'
```
:::
:::

::: paragraph
or, if you use idRef:
:::

::: listingblock
::: content
``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
curl --location --request PUT '/api/v2/parcel/idref/{idRef}'
```
:::
:::

[Request Body ]{.clickonme}

::: content
::: listingblock
::: content
``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
                            
                                {
                                    "plan": {
                                      "code": "HANDS"
                                    },
                                    "parcel": {
                                      "type":"T2H",
                                      "size":"S"
                                    },
                                    "receiver": {
                                      "name": "test name",
                                      "companyName": "test lastName",
                                      "address": {
                                          "countryCode": "LT",
                                          "locality":"Vilnius",
                                          "postalCode": "08247",
                                          "street": "Juozo Balčikonio g.",
                                          "building": "5"
                                      },
                                      "contacts":{
                                          "phone":"+37000000000",
                                          "email": "test@test.lt"
                                      }
                                    }
                                  }
                            
                        
```
:::
:::
:::

#### 3. Initiate step

::: paragraph
When the parcel is successfully prepared, you can complete the shipment
creation process and initiate it.
:::

::: listingblock
::: content
``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
curl --location --request POST '/api/v2/shipping/initiate'
```
:::
:::

[Request Body ]{.clickonme}

::: content
::: listingblock
::: content
``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
                            
                                {"parcelIds": [{{parcelId}}]}
                            
                        
```
:::
:::
:::

[Request Body by idRef ]{.clickonme}

::: content
::: listingblock
::: content
``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
                            
                                {"idRefs": [{{IdRef}}]}
                            
                        
```
:::
:::
:::

[Response Body ]{.clickonme}

::: content
::: listingblock
::: content
``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
                            
                                {
                                    "requestId": "04d811ee-6b97-3778-95bd-ed123021001c"
                                }
                            
                        
```
:::
:::
:::

#### 4. Get shipping order status

::: paragraph
To ensure the successful creation of the shipment and obtain its
tracking number, you can utilize the requestId obtained after initiating
the shipment in the previous step.
:::

::: listingblock
::: content
``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
curl --location --request GET '/api/v2/shipping/status/{requestId}'
```
:::
:::

[Response Body ]{.clickonme}

::: content
::: listingblock
::: content
``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
                            
                                {
                                    "status": "SUCCESSFUL",
                                    "items": [
                                        {
                                            "barcode": "CH800063274LT",
                                            "parcelId": 3499918,
                                            "status": "OK",
                                            "trackable": true
                                        }
                                    ]
                                }
                            
                        
```
:::
:::
:::

#### 5. Print sticker step

::: paragraph
Generate a sticker in PDF format for the created shipment using the
parcelId obtained in Step 1. \*
:::

::: listingblock
::: content
``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
curl --location --request GET '/api/v2/sticker/pdf?parcelIds={{parcelId}}&layout=LAYOUT_10x15'
```
:::
:::

::: paragraph
or, if you use idRef:
:::

::: listingblock
::: content
``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
curl --location --request GET '/api/v2/sticker/pdf?idRefs={{idRefs}}&layout=LAYOUT_10x15'
```
:::
:::

::: paragraph
\* Please note that this is a simple example, and there are additional
options available to tailor shipment generation to your specific needs
and scenarios. You can customize parameters accordingly; detailed
information is available in the provided documentation.
:::
:::

#### [](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_create){.anchor}[2.3.1. create](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_create){.link} {#_create}

::: paragraph
`POST /api/v2/parcel`
:::

::: paragraph
Create parcel
:::

::: note
Please note that with this method, you only create a parcel. To clarify,
you add the shipment data to the cart, but you do not complete the
shipment creation process. In order for the parcel to be ready for
shipment and to complete the creation process, it must be initiated. The
shipping initiation method is described in the
\"[initiateShipping](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_initiateshipping)\"
section.
:::

::: sect2
::: paragraph
It is possible to update, before initiate call, parcel (by id or idRef)
information such as: address, plan, size, weight, services and etc.\
Parcel update endpoint request has same structure as Parcel create, json
fields **will override current parcel data**.
:::

::: paragraph
Services field will behave differently, as list it will not override it,
but add new items. **Example below**
:::
:::

::: paragraph
`PUT /api/v2/parcel/{parcelId}`
:::

::: paragraph
Update parcel

##### [](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_samples_24){.anchor}[Samples](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_samples_24){.link} {#_samples_24}
:::

::: {.olist .loweralpha}
a.  Sample update request:

    ::: listingblock
    ::: content
    ``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
    curl --location --request PUT '<hostname>/api/v2/parcel/000000' \
                                                --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
                                                --header 'Authorization: Bearer <authorization access token>' \
                                                --data-raw '{
                                                    ...
                                                    "services": [
                                                        {
                                                            "id": 2
                                                        }
                                                    ]
                                                }'
    ```
    :::
    :::

b.  Get parcel by id response

    ::: listingblock
    ::: content
    ``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
    {
            ...
            "services": [
                {
                    "id": 2,
                    "code": "C_PIRM_LAISK",
                    "included": false
                }
            ]
        }
    ```
    :::
    :::

c.  Sample second update request:

    ::: listingblock
    ::: content
    ``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
    curl --location --request PUT '<hostname>/api/v2/parcel/000000' \
        --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
        --header 'Authorization: Bearer <authorization access token>' \
        --data-raw '{
            ...
            "services": [
                {
                    "id": 1
                }
            ]
        }'
    ```
    :::
    :::

d.  Get parcel by id response

    ::: listingblock
    ::: content
    ``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
    {
            ...
            "services": [
                {
                    "id": 1,
                    "code": "C_REG_LAISK&BIG",
                    "included": false
                },
                {
                    "id": 2,
                    "code": "C_PIRM_LAISK",
                    "included": false
                }
            ]
        }
    ```
    :::
    :::

e.  **Note**: also `"services": []` will override existing data. But
    `null` will not:

    ::: paragraph
    Request
    :::

    ::: listingblock
    ::: content
    ``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
    curl --location --request PUT '<hostname>/api/v2/parcel/000000' \
        --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
        --header 'Authorization: Bearer <authorization access token>' \
        --data-raw '{
            ...
            "services": null
        }'
    ```
    :::
    :::

    ::: paragraph
    Response
    :::

    ::: listingblock
    ::: content
    ``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
    {
            ...
            "services": [
                {
                    "id": 1,
                    "code": "C_REG_LAISK&BIG",
                    "included": false
                },
                {
                    "id": 2,
                    "code": "C_PIRM_LAISK",
                    "included": false
                }
            ]
        }
    ```
    :::
    :::

    ::: paragraph
    Request
    :::

    ::: listingblock
    ::: content
    ``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
    curl --location --request PUT '<hostname>/api/v2/parcel/000000' \
        --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
        --header 'Authorization: Bearer <authorization access token>' \
        --data-raw '{
            ...
            "services": []
        }'
    ```
    :::
    :::

    ::: paragraph
    Response
    :::

    ::: listingblock
    ::: content
    ``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
    {
            ...
            "services": []
        }
    ```
    :::
    :::
:::
:::

##### [](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_description_29){.anchor}[Description](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_description_29){.link} {#_description_29}

::: paragraph
To initiate dispatch of parcels. The response returns the identification
numbers of shipping item carts. It is important to mention that when
initiating shipments, they need to be grouped: UNISEND (LP EXPRESS)
parcels and Lithuanian postal service parcels. But if you initiate at
one time parcels with Lithuanian postal services and UNISEND (LP
EXPRESS) services - then no statuses will appear after the initiation
(there will be PENDING)
:::
:::

You can submit one or multiple original shipment barcodes in a single
request. For each provided barcode, the system will return a
corresponding return barcode
:::

::: paragraph
To call a courier for individual shipping items. Check callCourier
endpoint if courier call is possible.
:::

::: note
Please note that by default, the courier is called automatically after
each time you create a shipment. If you prefer to use the callCourier
method and invite the courier at a time convenient for you, please
contact us via email at <api-manosiuntos@post.lt> to enable this option.
:::

::: paragraph
To get the **full shipping cost** including customs duty and
administration fees:\
In the
[EstimateShippingOperations](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_estimateshippingoperations)
endpoints (POST methods), add the documents object (same structure as
used in shipment creation).

It is mandatory to provide:

-   hsCode (6, 8, or 10 digits)
-   countryCode (country of origin)

These fields are required in order to calculate the exact total price.
:::

[Example: Request to get the full shipping cost including customs duty
and administration fees]{.clickonme}

::: content
::: listingblock
::: content
``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
                                POST: /api/v2/shipping/estimate/price/list
                                
                                {
                                "senderAddressId": 0,
                                "items": [
                                    {
                                        "id": "123",
                                        "receiverCountryCode": "US",
                                        "receiverPostalCode": "14331",
                                        "size": "S",
                                        "weight": 10,
                                        "partCount": 1,
                                        "planCode": "TRACKED",
                                        "parcelType": "P2H",
                                        "documents": {
                                            "cn": {
                                                "contentType": "GIFT",
                                                "parts": [
                                                    {
                                                        "summary": "Knyga",
                                                        "weight": 5,
                                                        "quantity": 1,
                                                        "hsCode": 123456,
                                                        "amount": 999,
                                                        "currencyCode": "EUR",
                                                        "countryCode": "LT"
                                                    }
                                                ]
                                            }
                                        },
                                        "services": [
                                            {
                                                "code": "null",
                                                "value": "null"
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                                
                            
```
:::
:::
:::

[Example: Response with the full shipping cost, including customs duty
and administration fees]{.clickonme}

::: content
::: listingblock
::: content
``` {.CodeRay .highlight}
                                
                                [
                                {
                                    "id": "123",
                                    "price": {
                                        "amount": 8.45,
                                        "currency": "EUR"
                                    }
                                }
                                ]
                                
                            
```
:::
:::
:::

::: sect4
::: note
**For shipments to the USA, the following requirements apply:**

1.  Additional contract agreement.
2.  User consent to pay customs duty and administration fees.
3.  In Self-Service, API v2 users must edit their profile and check "I
    agree to pay customs duty and commission fee" (one-time action).
4.  If consent is given → user can create shipments to the USA via API
    v2 and self-service.
5.  If not → shipments to the USA are blocked, except for "documents
    only", which can be created without customs declaration.

Users can check duty fee amounts using the new duty/estimate/price and
existing shipping/estimate/price endpoints.
:::
:::
:::
:::

##### [](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_description_29){.anchor}[Description](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_description_29){.link} {#_description_29}

::: paragraph
To initiate dispatch of parcels. The response returns the identification
numbers of shipping item carts. It is important to mention that when
initiating shipments, they need to be grouped: UNISEND parcels and
Lithuanian postal service parcels. But if you initiate at one time
parcels with Lithuanian postal services and UNISEND services - then no
statuses will appear after the initiation (there will be PENDING)
:::
:::

::: paragraph
Address API public documentation.\
To understand what addresses look like, we have 3 types of addresses:\
With streets and buildings, e.g., Dariaus ir Girėno g. 7, 74119
Jurbarkas\
Without streets and buildings, e.g., Ūta, Rumšiškių sen., Kaišiadorių r.
sav. 56370\
With buildings without streets, e.g., 1, 88316 Kairiai (Telšių r. sav.)
:::

## [](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_tracking){.anchor}[5. Tracking](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_tracking){.link} {#_tracking}

::: sectionbody
::: paragraph
Possibility to track some of the items by barcode depends on which plan
you have selected. When parcel are delivered (PARCEL_DELIVERED) or
cancelled (PARCEL_CANCELED) we recommend to stop tracking because there
will be no new events anyway. Tracking main status is returned in
**publicStateType** field.
:::

+----------------------+----------------------+-----------------------+
| Plan Code            | Destination country  | Trackable             |
+======================+======================+=======================+
| UNTRACKED            | ANY                  | false                 |
+----------------------+----------------------+-----------------------+
| SIGNED               | LT                   | true                  |
+----------------------+----------------------+-----------------------+
| SIGNED               | ANY except LT        | false                 |
+----------------------+----------------------+-----------------------+
| TERMINAL             | LT,LV,EE             | true                  |
+----------------------+----------------------+-----------------------+
| TERMINAL             | ANY except LT        | false                 |
+----------------------+----------------------+-----------------------+
| TRACKED              | ANY except LT        | true                  |
+----------------------+----------------------+-----------------------+
| HANDS                | ANY                  | true                  |
+----------------------+----------------------+-----------------------+

::: sect2
### [](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_updv_tracking_paths){.anchor}[5.1. Paths](https://www.post.lt/savitarna/api_doc.html#_updv_tracking_paths){.link} {#_updv_tracking_paths}
